animal.description:
I am ready for a spirited new beginning and how about you?
Boooo!  My name is Ghost and I really am the friendliest ghost you would ever hope to meet.  I am happy, lively, and quite a comical fellow.  I am a sprightly, fun fusion of Boxer and Husky and at only 2 1/2 years old - yes, I am an active guy and at only around 45 pounds I am a great sized bundle of fun.  
I'm not looking to haunt a mansion but I definitely need a hang out with a secure fenced yard so I can run and play and haunt to my heart's content.  I love my toys and I love to play with my doggy friends and would so love to have a doggy sib to keep me busy and out of trouble.  I do quite well with the kitty friends as well.  I've had a lot to learn in this new and wonderful re-birth here and have been busy at working hard on all those humanly type manner things but I still do need lots of patience, a sense of humour and positive handling from my spirit guides to be my best self.   
Now!  If you are ready to learn more and possibly haunt along with friendly, comical, sprightly me please review the details on how we might possibly haunt together!

Ghost's adoption fee is $400.  He has been neutered, fully vaccinated, heart worm & tick diseases tested negative & preventatives given for the season.  Please review his bio and  If you feel you are the special person or family to welcome Ghost into your heart and home **PLEASE COMPLETE** the application found at this link - https://form.jotform.com/72823870527260  to open discussions and learn more about our rescue and adoption process.  A volunteer will be happy to help you and we just request your patience as we are volunteers doing our best to handle all the day to day needs of our dogs, our busy rescue and our families. 
**PLEASE NOTE** that we adopt only within the province of Ontario and preference will be given to potential adopters within our local areas provided they qualify and are the best fit for our dog.
Thanks everyone!

Miss Sophia is a previous St. Cloud Rescue dog that was adopted and recently returned, due to a family moving.  Sophia has been loved and lived with a family with children.  Sophia is a gorgeous full Saint Bernard that is approximately 6 years old.  Sophia does well with most dogs, however, she would also do well as an only dog.  Either can work depending on how the dogs react to each other.  Sophia weighs approximately 120 pounds and is current on all vaccinations, spayed, heartworm negative and housetrained.  She enjoys baths and doesn’t mind having her nails clipped.  If you have ever dreamed of a beautiful, show quality Saint, Sophia could be your dream companion.

In concern for families with small children, we will not adopt a dog to a home with any child under the age of 5. This is due to the large size of Saint Bernards and the safety of your children. Our Saint Bernards are not aggressive or mean in any way, they can just knock down children easily. If you would like to visit our pups please contact St. Cloud's Rescue at www.stcloudsrescue.org or call 972-679-5319. The first step in adopting from St. Cloud's Rescue is to complete an application. The application may be found OUR WEBSITE at www.stcloudsrescue.org. Please click on the application process, complete and then email it. Once the application has been sent please call us to confirm that we have received it. St.Cloud's Rescue maintains the right to deny applications to anyone for any reason we see fit. St. Cloud Rescue is a non-profit 501-c-3 organization. St. Clouds Rescue requires new owners to purchase a one year supply of heartworm preventative from us, which is at cost. We require a home visit prior to all placements. All our dogs must be microchipped at a cost of $20.00. There is a $250.00 donation fee. All dogs adopted through St Clouds Rescue must be indoors. St. Bernards can not tolerate the Texas heat.

animal.description:
Toby is a 2-year-old Longcoat GSD who is looking for an experienced handler. The shelter where he was dumped at only said he lived outside with a pack of dogs. Four wood walls and to many other lonely dogs is the only thing he has known. It was obvious that toby had very little human interaction. Toby is house trained and crate trained and has a strange connection with a certain orange ball. We are looking for a home with someone who is wanting to spend time working and training him as he is behind where he should be. He was never socialized around people or places and this has him fearful at first, so he will need a handler who will make him feel safe and keep strangers informed. He also will need a home with carpeting, he can not walk on hardwood or tile floors. Due to the fact he is a little uncoordinated and not use to it. His favorite things to do are playing fetch and playing in the water of any kind especially the baby pool. Since Toby is not comfortable in public a fenced in yard is a must. He needs training walking on a leash and can be hesitant in public places so a quiet neighborhood is recommended. He is good with other dogs of all sizes outside the home but he will need to be the only dog for now.. We are not sure about cats, but he doesn't seem to have a prey drive, can get excited seeing one once in a while but mostly - ignores them. A home with no children is recommended. Toby is a happy boy and loves being in the house with his foster mom, he has so much potential with the right person. 

Please visit our website at http://www.gsror.com/adoptionapp/ to complete an online application.

animal.description:
Sweet Tiffany just turned a year old. She was rescued as a stray from the streets in Houston Texas at the age of just 2 months and brought to Colorado. Adopted quickly because of her remarkable beauty and spunky personality, Tiffany was reported as a wonderful puppy with tons of energy and a passion for long hikes and playing in her back yard. Tiffany is now crate trained and potty trained. She is highly intelligent and quickly picks up basic commands such as sit, lay down, off, leave it, stay, and release. She is motivated by both praise and treats. Tiffany has a goofy personality and quickly bonds with new people. Tiffany wll guard your yard intently from any resident squirrels or neighboring cats, so her prey drive would prevent her from living harmoniosly with any canine friends. 

As an adolscent, Tiffany was unfortunately, attacked by another dog. She can (understandably) be a bit leary if strange dogs approach her inappropriately or too quickly, but she has since learned to start trusting her handlers and quickly warms now once she is properly introduced to new friends! Tiffany would thrive in a home with a yard to run in and a family that will keep her entertained and occupied. She does enjoy her downtime in her crate and has no issue keeping herself calm/occupied. Tiffany thrives on the attention from her favorite people and will certainly fill any home completely with copious amounts of love and loyalty. 

Please do not hesitate to reach out if you are interested in meeting or learning more about this sweet gal that deserves a second chance in a home where she feels loved and protected! She is waiting to meet you!

	Spay/Neuter

animal.description:
Hi my name is Prometheus and I am a 5 year old Anatolian Shepherd. I am a gentle giant weighing apx 140lbs.. I am good with other dogs and I seem to be very fond of men. I love women too but I really enjoy my guy buddies and hanging out in the man cave. 

I was left at the shelter by my original owner with a note that she couldn’t keep me. Just left me out front outside of the shelter :( 

It’s hard to believe anyone could do that to me since I am such a good, kind and silly guy.

Perhaps it’s the congenital abnormalities in my rear legs that she, and adoption applicants have turned away from? 

My rear knees knock together due to my knees and hips being out due to bad breeding and congenital abnormalities subsequent because of it. I am not a candidate for orthopedic surgery or my rescue would have done it. 

Honestly, I am not very bothered by my legs and I still play,  go for walks or just chill on my big cushiony bed. 

If you are interested in adopting me please first complete an adoption application at: www.delaneysdog.com/adoption-application.html

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Interested in adopting? If so, please complete an adoption application first at www.delaneysdog.com/adoption-application.html

All Delaney's Dog adoption fees include :
-Up-to-date vaccinations
**Puppies receive 3 sets of DHPP & rabies vaccine. 
-Spay/neuter
-Microchip & microchip registration

The adoption process requires an initial approved Adoption Application, a home visit to ensure safety and well-being of adoptee & a separate Adoption Agreement.

**Adoption fees vary and are NOT NEGOTIABLE. 

NOTE: An Adoption Application does not guarantee an adoption. Adoptions are based on the best possible situation for each dog and their prospective owners. Not all breeds are right for all people and not all people are right for all breeds. Our commitment is to place these animals in the right homes so that they never again have to face re-homing. They deserve a forever family too.

Additionally, each adoption includes a one week, partial fee refundable, trial period to ensure pet is a right fit.

NO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS

animal.description: Maggie is a little leery of strangers, but very lovable once she gets to know a person and they've earned her trust. She's great with other dogs of all sizes and loves to play and wrestle with them. She does not require a ton of exercise, but does love to go for walks and play ball or tug. She's the perfect mix of active and lazy. She would do best in a home with no young children. She requires a slow, steady approach from people and can be a bit defensive to a fast approach from a person who has not gained her trust. Ongoing training will be necessary as she settles into her new home. She is a smart girl and very motivated by food, and is fun to train with. She is crate trained and is almost completely potty trained. Getting her on a routine quickly will make her potty training easy to finish. Foster will assist with her transition into the right home, including help with training.

animal.description:
Hi,

My name is Harriet! I came from a tough situation in Alabama, but found myself in really nice place with lots of hoomans that are looking after me. During dis crazy pandemic, I went to stay wit a foster family for a while. My foster mom got to know me real good. She says I'm special because I like all da attention for myself.

I liked to play with my foster broda but he was the only one (mom says he was a basset mix, whatever dat is!) I didn't like my foster sister or my tiny foster broda. If dey have da treats...I wants dem and I will take dem when foster mom's not looking! That's when we have problems even with my basset friend. Oh, I also don't like da cats, dey make me bark a lot!

What can foster mom tell you about me? Well, I'm real good at finding squirrels! I will bark when I pick up on a scent, cuz dat's my job! I like my elbows scratched and I like kisses on my nose! I like to look up and see what's all around me, Foster mom thinks dat's silly!

When it's thundering out, I get scared, so mom puts dis weird thundershirt on me, but I feel better when she does! I like to snuggle when I'm scared and will lie on top of you.

I needs help with da potty business, so mom got me some really pretty diapers to wear. Most days I don't needs dem, but as soon as I am done eating, I have to be told to go outside or I forget myself and have an accident. Foster Mom says I need lots of one on one time wit my furever family. She says she wishes for me to be an only furbaby, cuz she thinks that's best. She thinks I deserve lots and lots of attention.

I would love to go for walks wit you and shows you where da squirrels are hiding. I am really smart too, but I need help to learn new things, can you believes I don't know how to sits? I need lots of love, and have lots of love to give.

Love,
Harriet Primary Color: Tri Color Weight: 53lbs Age: 11yrs 1mths 4wks Animal has been Spayed

animal.description:
Buddy is a loving pup who is searching for the perfect home. Buddy came from a neglectful situation and is fearful of many people at first. He will take time to build a strong, trusting bond with his person. For this reason, we will require multiple visits with Buddy prior to him being adopted and therefore applicants local to the Des Moines area (or close) are preferred. His ideal home would be with a patient and experienced owner, no young children, and a fenced in yard (Buddy will take time to trust new people putting a leash on him). Buddy does well with other dogs after a proper introduction, but would prefer a furry friend to be lower energy like himself. Buddy is well house trained, but does not prefer the kennel. He is not destructive so gets free range of his foster home. Buddy also has had a couple seizures and is currently on phenobarbital (roughly $30 per month prescription). Buddy is around 30 pounds and 4 years old. His adoption fee is $250. Apply at www.foreverhomedogs.org to meet him!All adoptions are $200 per dog which include spay/neuter, micro-chipped and up-to-date on required shots. 

Senior dogs, at our discretion, are adopted out at $100 per dog because we know they will have less time with your family and may eventually have more needs as they get older. But we feel these dogs deserve to live out the rest of their lives as part of a loving family.

I'm called Snuggles - I have two speeds - sleeping and playing. I love to play with toys, other dogs and be active, but at the end of the day, I like to cuddle on the sofa. animal.description:
Only local adoptions in the St. Louis / Metro IL area! 

Hydee is a beautiful terrier mix, approximately 2-4 years old. She is medium in height and weighs 50lbs. Hydee has lived most of her life on the streets. We followed her for weeks through the dangerous streets of St. Louis and after a lot of careful planning, finally trapped her. She spent a lot of time at Hyde Park, hence the name Hydee. She has acclimated to becoming a house dog very well. Of course it took a lot of time and patience because she was scared and not too trusting. We quickly learned food was the key to her heart.  

Hydee’s perfect family would be someone who has the understanding and patience needed to acclimate a shy and skittish dog to a new environment. We prefer Hydee have a tall privacy fence. We believe she will do well with another dog in the home as long as the dog is calm and mellow. We also believe Hydee will do well with older kids or teens but feel young kids and toddlers may be too overwhelming for her. She is house and kennel trained and loves being a couch potato. Hydee also loves to go on walks but would need a quiet park or neighborhood because loud noises will scare her. 

Hydee is a very sweet girl. She loves her foster family and has bonded very well with them. We are looking for a forever family that she can do the same with. 

Hydee’s, adoption fee is $275. This includes spay, vaccines, microchip, dewormer and maintaining heartworm prevention while in our care. Hydee also went through heartworm treatment and it will be crucial for her to be on monthly prevention. 

If you would like to be selected for a meeting with our girl, please submit an online adoption application by copying the link below into your browser. 

https://form.jotformpro.com/50153632350949

animal.description:
This is Max he is a sweet older guy that has been through a lot in his life. He was rescued as a pup from an abusive home. He had a home until addiction took over his life. 

Max attaches himself to his person and beside them all the time. We have had him for a bit getting him used to all the commotion of an active house. He wants to eat in the bedroom because that is where he was eating in the dark. He seems sad when his person leaves for an extended period of time but bounces back when back to routine. He is very much about routine and knows the feeding schedule and makes sure you do not forget it is time to give him yummys... he bounces around and barks. He sleeps with my daughter on her bed along with her cat. That being said he gets along with dogs and cats. He likes being part of the pack and still has play in him. 

He is such a sweet boy who deserves to relax and enjoy his life.

All Dallas DogRRR adoptable pets are spayed or neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines upon finalizing adoption. The standard minimum donation for puppies is $325 + 8.25% tax = $351.81, for dogs over 12 months the adoption fee is $225 + 8.25% tax = $243.66 and for our senior dogs 8 years and up is $100 + 8.25% tax = $108.25; this increase includes sales tax recently required by the State of Texas to collect. You can view all the adoptable pets and fill out an adoption application online on our website at http://dallasdogrrr.org. 

For more information, you can email adopt@dallasdogrrr.org. Upon receiving your application please allow us 2-3 business days to review and process.

animal.description:
Meet Hasso!!! Hasso is a 6 month old pup who has had a rough go of things after being hit by a car at 10 weeks old, leaving him temporarily partially paralyzed. But he is not a pooch that’s going to let some little thing like paralysis get him down! He made a remarkable recovery and can now walk, run, jump and do almost everything that any other pup can do!

Because he is improving, we can’t say if he will make a full recovery or not. But all this means is that he may need to wear a belly band and diaper in the house. Similar to having a toddler :) 

All Hasso wants now is to find a home to call his own with a person or family that will love him. Will you be that home?

animal.description:
Jethro and Rose are two awesome dogs that find themselves homeless and in need. Bonded, together since puppies their family moved away and couldn’t take them. They are all that's left and want to stay together. They need our help and asking a family out there to open up their home in welcoming them into their lives, so they can remain together.


Jethro (black) is approx. 7-9 years old, 67 pounds, who is shy at first, but then loves to be petted, head scratches and enjoys plenty of attention; from people. Jethro is sweet and loving. He loves giving handshakes. He is gentle and tolerates young children well. Loves going on walks, enjoys the water, plays a little with toys but then loses interest quickly, but enjoys play with his sister. Jethro along with his sister Rose were raised as outside dogs all of their lives but we won’t adopt outside dogs so in his foster home he has quickly learned to live inside and enjoys indoor living. He will alert you when he has to go potty and is house broken. Jethro is learning cues like sit, stay and come and already shakes. He and his sibling will require a large fenced yard where he can stretch his legs when not going on walks to run off energy. Jethro is not fond of other male dogs but he does well with females. Jethro is not good with cats. Jethro unfortunately did test positive for heartworms but he is currently undergoing treatment at no cost to the potential adopter. Jethro is deserving and would love a forever home with his most loyal companion his sister Rose.

We are currently accepting application for Jethro and Rose to apply please go to complete our online pre-adoption application

Jethro and Rose have been spayed/neutered, up-to-date on all vaccines, heartworm tested; Rose placed on prevention and Jethro undergoing heartworm treatment currently. Both will be microchipped before going to their forever home. Both will be available to go to a home once Jethro has completed his treatment.

Hi my name is Monty and I was adopted  from PAAW.  My owner loves me, but due to changes in her life, she will no longer have enough time for me and wants to find a good home for me.  

I am used to having a home where I am loved and well fed.  I am house trained.

We are working on basic commands and walking well on a leash.

If you are looking for a best friend just to hang out with you I am your guy.

animal.description:
03/02/20 - Ranger Mouse may be an older gentleman at 13, but he's still very spry and full of life! He wags his whole body, not just his tail, and he's pretty much in a state of perpetual wag when you're petting him. He rubs his whole body on you and gives lots of kisses. He's still able to jump on and off the couch and bed. However ...

We found him as a malnourished stray (no microchip or tags) with horribly infected teeth in Jan 2019. When we took him to be neutered it was found that his testicles had never descended. This can cause health issues so he needed to have exploratory surgery to have them removed. He gained weight and we were able to to do his neuter surgery, and a dental surgery to do a full mouth extraction by a canine dental specialist due to his fragile jaw.

Early on he was having seizures and we felt we could help him overcome them. We have been working with our vet to control them with medications. But we are continuing to need to change the doses and get him ongoing blood work (monitors his internal organs for possible issues with the medication). Unfortunately his seizures continue despite the medication. 
** We have chosen to call him a Forever Friend and put him into Hospice care with his foster. **

We are asking his friends and followers for donations for his continued care of anti seizure and anti nausea medications, blood work and special diet. 

If you can help our group give Ranger Mouse continued hospice care we would be very grateful. There are several ways to donate:

1. Via PayPal directly - https://www.paypal.com/us/fundraiser/charity/1432464

2. Via Facebook using this link and clicking the ""Donate"" button under the cover photo (on right) which allows Facebook Pay, PayPal or credit card one-time or monthly donations - 
https://www.facebook.com/ForgottenFriendsMixBreedRescue/

3. Via check sent to below:

Forgotten Friends
c/o Deborah Ullrich
P. O. Box 1395
Leander, Texas 78641
 
NOTE: We are a 501c(3) organization so all donations are tax deductible.

animal.description:
I am 60 lbs., 4 years old, and l am looking for my forever home.

Adoption Donation: $350

All dogs are microchipped, neutered, current on all vaccines, heartworm tested and started on Tri Heart Plus; Vectra 3D.

All household members and any dogs from the household need to be present at the time of the adoption.

Our website is always kept 100% up to date with who is currently available.  As soon as animals are adopted, they are moved to the Adopted Pets page so if they are still listed on the Adoptable Dogs or Cats page, they are still available. So keep any eye on the site for any animals being added as available for adoption as new animals are added everyday! We would recommend if you haven’t done so already that you submit a general online adoption application with us so it is on file for when you are ready to come out and adopt. The adoption counselors will be able to show you many that would be a good fit for your family. Animal House Shelter can not guarantee breed or breed mix of our adoptable animals. DEWY - AVAILABLE IN THE MIDWEST AND NEW ENGLAND (Due to new state regulations, Lucky Lab Rescue and Adoption can not adopt dogs to owners who live in the state of Massachusetts.)

Dewy is a handsome Lab/Shepherd mix puppy. Under a year old this, calm, smart puppy will probably soon grow to be 65-70 lbs. Dewey is neutered, up to date on vaccinations, heartworm negative, and kept on monthly preventatives. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an adoption application on www.luckylabrescue.com and indicate “Dewey” in the notes section.

animal.description:
Meet Duke! 

Learning, curious, loving once he knows you. 

Duke is a very big, fun loving guy that is still learning a few things here at the center. With an experienced dog owner and someone willing to put in a little time, he can begin his transition home. He is over 100 lbs so his new owner will need to be able to physically handle 110 lbs of fun on a leash. 

In the meantime, he's learning how to greet other dogs and new people. He's also working on his weight. So far, he's lost a lot of weight since he arrived and is looking and feeling much better! Whew! Feels pretty awesome to shed some pounds. He can move now! 

Give us a shout to learn more about Duke's needs. After a meeting or two with our trainers and a little extra time getting to know him..... he'll warm your heart. He's a character! 

His ideal home is low stimulus with an active, calm, loving leader. Duke comes with ongoing post adoption support and a team of people ready to help you and your new co-pilot build a bond geared for success!

animal.description:
Meet Patches! 

Friendly, senior, good energy! 

This sweet guy didn't get the memo that he's 12! He still has a lot of life in him and loves his walks! He's friendly and loving, yet with a little bit of an independent side too. Patches is friendly with other dogs while on leash. Due to his age though, he should only come into contact with calm, dog friendly dogs. Inside the home, he really loves his toys and treats to himself so he has asked to be the only apply of your eye. No other dogs in the home please. 

This boy is such an explorer and really loves to get out and sniff around. He's very well behaved inside the home and would love nothing more than to keep you company during the day! He can help with yard work, watching your favorite TV show and so much more. Have an extra spot on your couch and in your heart for a wonderful senior companion? Patches may be your guy! 

Ahhh, with the joys of older age comes sensitives to being touched on his back legs and back end. So no children for that reason though he can greet children well. 

We love this boy. He's ready to go home!

animal.description: Scout is a loving, energetic, 5-yr. old girl who absolutely adores her humans. She was pregnant when she came to Furkids' shelter. All of her puppies were adopted, but Scout is still waiting patiently at the shelter for her perfect match - she is our longest term resident! Scout is a dog who loves a project, and she spends her time outside re-arranging the yards; she loves to move big sticks around and feels like she has accomplished something grand every day! She is looking for a home where she is the only animal so that she can be the center of attention. She also needs to go to a home where she will be actively worked with every day, as this girl really needs to feel like she is adding value. After finishing her work, however, she is available for lots of cuddles and lots of treats! Scout weighs 52 lbs. and her estimated birthdate is 3/14/2015. If you want to know more about Scout and to speak to an Adoption Counselor, please complete a survey at https://furkids.org/dog-adoptions/application. At this time, meeting our dogs is by appointment only. After submitting a survey, an adoption counselor will contact you to give you more information about the dog you are interested in adopting and to arrange for you to meet the dog. Must be at least 21 years of age to adopt.

SHAYE is a border collie/boxer/pit mix & is hoping for a new home where he is the only guy in town! He’s been thriving at Glen Highland Farms in Gloucester VA.  with lots of love and attention, as well as plenty of toy play, but like every sweet BC mix we know, this one wants his own people! Shaye is a youngster at 11, full of energy for a great ball game or long walk, a true lover of the great outdoors. He’s full of personality, curiosity and confidence, fine meeting anyone and everyone. Belly rubs are his favorites! Stimulating Shaye’s great brain is easy with food puzzles and trick training cause he’s happy to learn and eager to do well! He is rather selective with dogs so best as a solo boy and not a dog park dog, plus he requires a fenced yard. Shaye is about 45 pounds and good with cats. He has allergies to certain food and grasses so is on daily medication to prevent flare-ups.
Prior to GHF, he was in a MD shelter from someone who could not manage his needs well.

Notes:  

At heart Tucker is a very sweet boy, and he forms very strong bonds with people that he trusts.  Unfortunately, over the years he has learned to not trust people as easily as he once did.  It takes time to build that bond and we are hoping to find someone who is committed to continuing his training to make him feel safe and secure, while giving him a loving and structured environment he needs.   He has food/kennel aggression and he fear bites (no one has been severely injured by him). We are working with him on training to correct his behaviors. With time and patience we are hoping he will learn that not all people will be mean to him. He has specific triggers that we are working to either avoid or correct through the training. Sadly he is staying at our facility at this time so he is not getting one on one training with the same person. We are actively trying to get him into a foster home that can work with him. He is okay with some dogs and cats but not all. Due to his previous bite history he cannot go to a home with young children. If you are interested in more information on Tucker please email caawsmail@yahoo.com.

If you are interested in adopting this animal please go here to find out how and fill out our app online: http://www.caaws.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Blue and his sister Lady lived on chains for 13 years!!!  Lady’s health was deteriorating and an animal lover who lived nearby was able to convince the owners to surrender her so that she could get proper vet care and TLC in a home environment. The person sadly had to leave Blue behind and the poor guy was miserable.  Blue was crying and shaking after Lady had left . SNARR was asked to help Blue and we said yes. Blue had never been vetted, he was covered in fleas, a skin rash, Despite this rough life Blue has led, he’s the sweetest boy!!!! He loves to snuggle and needs to have his paw on you :-) He’s done remarkably well at adjusting to being inside, learning how to play, and he’s like a curious puppy exploring new things for the first time. He needs a fenced yard for sure, he’s never been off a chain.  For the first time yesterday he climbed on the couch! Now it’s his favorite place to hang out. Blue doesnt mind you dressing him up and is a ham for the camera. He’s great with kids but I think a older more calm atmosphere would be best for this old guy. Blue doesn’t do well with kitties so a home without cats is necessary. He likes to chase them. 
Could you be the special family that gives Blue the life he always deserved ??? Apply today at www.snarrnortheast.org

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING

**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $425 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
I'm Hans, a fun-sized Shepherd mix. I'm the perfect size, weighing about 40 lbs at 18 months old. My foster mom calls me her handsome little fox because of the markings on my face. I arrived from Texas about a month ago and although I'm shy with new people, I've found that learning new things helps me build that confidence I so need. My foster mom shows me lots of love and introduces me to new people all the time, so we are working on this.

Do you have another dog I could play with? I LOVE dogs and LOVE to play! That is when I am the happiest, actually. Chasing other dogs around the yard is totally my favorite thing to do! So, we've agreed that I definitely need to go to a home with another dog as it helps me build confidence. I also must go to a home with a fully fenced yard. Since I'm not totally trusting humans at this time, I could easily get scared and run.

Cats??? No problem! My foster mom has 3 of them and I totally ignore them. I even ignore the one that terrorizes the other dogs. I know what she is up to, she can't fool me! I am too smart for that. Kids? I will do well with older kids that dont move so fast and are patient with me. I am also 100% potty-trained and use the doggie door whenever I need to go outside. I have never had an accident in the house either.

That's another thing about me, I'm really smart! I catch on quick to routines and where everyone is supposed to go. So, I would excel in an agility course training as I love games of all kinds. I am still pretty scared of car rides as that was never part of my life, but the more I do it, the better I will be at it. My foster mom walks me everyday and I walk fantastic on a leash and follow her lead.

I use my crate as my little house I go to when Im scared, so please make sure you have a crate for me as I really enjoy that safe place to have.
I'm not gonna lie, new people scare me. So, when you meet me, I am going to be super shy. However, once I learn that I can trust you, I will be your forever friend. Can you provide a loving home for me to grow old in? If so, please apply!!

Apply here: https://www.fetchfosterandrescue.com/adopt

animal.description: Like a lot of us, this sweet, fuzzy-bear of a dog finds the world to be a little bit too much at times. If you know anyone who has sensory processing issues, you might be able to relate to Fulton. He is sensitive to noises and can be overwhelmed by new environments, but can thrive in a stable home and really blossoms once he learns to trust people. He enjoys the company of other calm animals and has lived with dogs and cats. He has shown us how he bonds very closely to his friends, and is a silly, playful, and affectionate pup. Fulton seems to have excellent manners in the home - he's very good about not getting up on furniture without being invited, doesn't get into things he shouldn't and isn't destructive, and sleeps quietly through the night in his crate. He will entertain you with his adorable antics like prancing around the yard like a pony, then bouncing over and sitting in front of you with the biggest smile on his face. He's the perfect pooch for someone who has a fenced yard and isn't into long walks around the 'hood. He feels safest in the house and prefers his potty breaks and play time to be in the backyard with you close by. He loves toys and is perfectly content to amuse himself when you're doing other things but likes hanging on the sofa watching Netflix if you want some company. If you would love to have a smile, a friendly nudge and some goofy company when you get home, Fulton is your guy. Because of his sensory issues, he is prone to the occasional meltdown (give us a holler about him and we can show you what that looks like) when new things become too much but in the right home, he'll not only be happy and content but you'll be delighted to have such a goofy, loyal, trusting companion. Fulton is also thriving in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Fulton has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Fulton is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told 'free,' coming when called and 'Place', which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once Fulton successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, he will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Fulton is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Fulton after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https://vimeo.com/89434193. Fulton has already picked up a lot of basic obedience and is even working on some advanced training to help him learn to deal with situations he finds stressful. Fulton is a gentle soul who is ready to find a loving home. Come meet this special pup! Follow Fulton on Instagram @omg_its_fulton

animal.description: Hi! My names Allie, I'm the longest resident here and I hope that it doesn't stay that way. I'm a little hesitant when I first meet you, only because it's just something that I just take time feeling comfortable with. Although, once I'm comfortable. Oh man am I so happy to be with you!! I do prefer to have my personal space when it comes to handling so that is why I recommend myself with a family with children no younger than 12. I do pull on leash but that's just because I'm SOO excited to get out and go for a run or walk, whichever you prefer, I'm just happy to be included. :) I love toys!! Squeaky toys, soft toys, tennis balls. Anything you can offer! I can play for hours upon hours! I also love treats; I would call myself treat motivated!! I'm a smart girl too... I know sit and shake with BOTH paws! How smart am I? I would call myself a couch dog too, just someone who can either go on a nice run at the park with OR someone you need to watch a good movie with, I can be there for you! On another topic, I am popular when it comes to meeting dogs here. In the beginning I was a little unsure, especially with approaching. I did relax with just co-existing with them though. Now, I do love to hangout with dogs on a shared fence-line. It's fun to meet new dogs all the time! But no cats!! I don't enjoy cats being in my presence, so I need a home without any cat companions! Overall, I think I do need an experienced home with leadership dedicated to training and exercise. Hope to meet you soon!

If you are looking for a quieter girl, one who will chill by your side, listening to your troubles - well, Natasha is the girl for you. She warms up to strangers at her own speed and once she decides they are friendly, she marks them in the friend column.

Natasha has good leash skills, has had some basic training and likes other dogs. She is a petite girl, perfect for a condo or townhome.

animal.description:
Who doesn't need a Blessing!? Petite with all the sweetness packed in to this package definitely makes her a gift. Blessing is 3 years old and ready for a loving home of her own. While in the shelter Blessing did well in playgroup with other large dogs with similar energy. 
She is sweet as she looks and walks fantastic on leash, she doesn't pull at all! I imagine her being a great gardening buddy because she loves to sniff all the flowers and can inspect your grass and dirt by having the time of her life rolling in it. She would make a great walking buddy too! She loves car rides and is treat motivated which will help with her training. She is a little dog focused so will need a family understanding of slow introductions and to take their time letting her decompress. She will need a home with NO small dogs or cats. She will need encouragement with basic commands, she has great energy and makes good eye contact which will help along the way. She is eager to learn! Blessing isn't a fan of a skateboarders passing by but doesn't mind bicycles at all. She is all smiles for people and loves to say hi. Ready for some Blessing in your life? Come by to meet her, she needs a foster or adopter to welcome her into a home life. She is house trained and crate trained. Has some basic obedience training and comes with free lessons.

animal.description:
Hellllo friends, it's me - Charlie Chaplin! I'm approximately 12 years old but don't let my age fool you, I am VERY active and strong. I weigh about 80 pounds and I am ready to sniff-sniff-sniff and follow my nose on all kinds of adventures, WITH YOU! I thoroughly enjoy going for long walks. Want a hiking buddy? I'm in, I'm no couch potato! In fact, I do very well in doggie daycare and would thrive in an active home with or without other dogs. Sorry, no cats, they are just too much fun for this ol' hound boy to chase.

I really LOVE being around people most of all and will lovingly follow you around. I love food, second-best to people! OK, maybe it's a tie! I am not food aggressive at all, but when I smell food - any kind of food - I get very excited and will do anything I can to get to the source of that wonderful smell! My foster mom crates me when she's cooking, for some reason she doesn't want my help! She also crates me when she's not at home, this stops me from helping myself to pantry - darn!

See, I am originally from Kentucky and was found as a stray. My foster mom surmises that I never lived in a home before and that I was an "outside dog" so all of the luxuries of a home environment were new to me when I arrived. I have been in my foster home since August though so I have learned so much! Yup, I'm ready for a forever family to take me the rest of the way! So whattya say?

Are you ready for some forever fun, with me?! Great! Please fill out an application today at www.northstarpets.org and ask for *UNWANTED HOUND SEEKING A HOME!

animal.description:
The head of a hound dog, the body of a Jack Russell, the speckled coat of a Cattle Dog, and a heart of gold! Mix all that together and you get Nigel! Nigel is a 2 year old stumpy-legged, big-headed super mutt who came to CCR from a shelter in the Western suburbs where he had been found stray. Nigel was absolutely petrified in the shelter, refusing to move or even make eye contact. We believed he was someone's pet who had ended up in a scary situation, so we took him back to CCR to do some behavior rehab. Jump forward a couple of weeks, and Nigel is not the shy, scared dog he used to be! Quite the opposite - Nigel is an active, social, friendly, exuberant, busy dog who loves attention and being treated like a little baby. Nigel is a terrier through and through - despite being under 30 pounds, Nigel can jump almost 6 feet in the air when he's excited enough! He loves to play fetch and tug with toys, and he has the Cattle Dog habit of nibbling your ankles and elbows when he wants you to get a move on! Nigel is housetrained and used to going in his crate at night. He loves to be in the middle of the action and is the kind of dog who will want to be wherever you are, whenever you're there. Nigel does not like other dogs or cats, so a home with a private fenced-in yard would be ideal, or a neighborhood where he won't have to see a lot of dogs constantly. His mouthy play style is too much for children, but he's the perfect addition to a home that loves terriers and all their smarts and energy. If you are looking for a busy bee to keep you on your toes, then Nigel is the man for you!

To meet Nigel, please submit an application at chicagocaninerescue.org!

animal.description:
I am perfect..

This gentle soul is Grant, a sweet, senior 11 year old Shihtzu Mix, with no permanent home or family.  Grant found himself in a animal shelter that specializes in Kittie Cats.  Even though he is not a Kitty, this Rescue helped him find Lone Star Shih Tzu and Lhasa Apso Rescue.  Grant is now healthy,  but has very limited vision. He uses his nose and other senses to get around, so a potential adopter should be aware of this and know that he likes to be near his human most of the time.

Grant has been having so much fun in his foster’s mommy’s home and she has learned much about him. Grant is good with other dogs, but he does not appreciate the youngsters getting in his face. An easy-going dog companion would be ok to have in his new home if they also respect his space.  He is super good overnight in a crate. And if you’re paying attention, you can tell when he needs to go potty.  

Grant has said he dreams of a fenced backyard so he can roam and explore safely, but prefers someone staying outside with him because he is comforted to always have a human close. This is also true inside the home. He is happy to follow you from room to room and settle wherever you are. Even though Grant is considered blind, once he gets used to his new home he navigates very well. A home with very little to no stairs will be required. 

His foster mommy says she will miss him very much since he is a nice doggy, even-tempered, and willing to please.

With just a few considerations Grant is just like any other dog. Please if you have it in your heart to add this sweetheart to your family, please let us know!

animal.description:
If you are interested in any of the dogs available at New Leash Rescue, you can reach out to the foster listed below for more information and then complete an adoption application which can be found at https://www.newleashrescue.org/adopt/policy.  Please email the completed application to newleashrescue2018@gmail.com

Wesley is a happy, snuggly, chatty AM Staffie who is looking for the right home.  He bonds quickly and will faithfully stay by your side.  He loves going for   leisurely walks and car rides. Loves to snuggle while being a couch potato with you.  When you need a good laugh, you can count on Wes to cheer you up.  If he wants attention or simply disagrees with what you're doing he will let you know in Wesley speak which is basically a mix of whining and screaming like an 80s rock singer but definitely not as loud.  He really is the perfect sidekick. 

Before you think you might be the perfect home for Wesley please understand he has some specific needs:  

These include:
- Wesley came to our rescue heartworm positive and went through treatment with our foster.  This means Wesley will need to be on heartworm preventive, given monthly from the vet, for the rest of his life.  The cost is about $10 a month.

- Wesley is not comfortable around young children and will growl and snap at them.  He needs a home with no children below the age of 14 yrs of age.  

- He requires slow introductions to dogs and may require up to a 2 week shut down period after adoption to feel comfortable in his new home.  This mostly applies to high energy dogs.  He does much better with older, chiller dogs.

- Wesley also has skin allergies.  He requires some medication and special shampoo, otherwise is prone to skin infections.  

Adoption fee is $350.00 + tax (no checks) 

Foster to contact: Ben & Tracy - tschlax@gmail.com or 612-750-7411

 Our fosters do the best they can to provide all information about the animal's background and temperament while in foster care in their home. An adopters routine and home environment are likely going to be different than that in their foster home. 

Sometimes there is more that comes out about a dog's personality once they have been able to settle in a home and truly become comfortable. There are great articles out there written about the different stages a pet goes through after adoption, discussing transitions that happen at 3 days, 3 weeks, and 3 months. We highly recommend reading about this - it will help you understand the transition your new pet goes through.

She will continue to be cared for under our Angel Pet program even after adoption until the issue has fully resolved. Sweet Pea loves to be outside, walks nicely on a leash, rides great in the car and absolutely loves going in the water! Any puddle, lake or stream will do! She has some food guarding issues so she needs an adult-only home with an experienced adopter. She likes other dogs and might be fine in a home with another dog if they can be separated at mealtimes and sharing of toys is managed while she settles into her new home. Sweet Pea is spayed, micro-chipped and up to date on vaccines. Her adoption fee is $350. If you would like to be Sweet Pea's new BFF, please email dogs@daws.org to arrange a meeting.

animal.description:
Do you have an active lifestyle? Do you love being outdoors for hours a day? Have you always wanted a dog that could learn lots of tricks and would do well with a job to do?
Kipper may be the dog for you!

Kipper is a HIGH HIGH energy boy who wants to play, play, play! He is a bit of a class clown that will provide endless entertainment. He would appreciate a yard with a TALL fence to show off his athleticism of leaping in the air and throwing toys for himself. (He can put his nose over the head of a 6ft tall person, it's impressive!)

Kipper would likely do best in a house rather than an apartment as he is not just big in personality, he is also just BIG! He is a 70 lb big clumsy boy who needs lots of space to stretch out.

He doesn't know what to think of kids and would likely knock them down with his enthusiasm.

Family visit: Required
Dog to dog: Required
Child integration score: moderate

animal.description:
Smushie is a staff favorite. If you are looking for a cuddly, affectionate, love bug, Smushie is your girl. She knows most of her basic commands, although her down is a bit unconventional, as she will stretch her back legs outs out, and look more like a frog than a dog. Smushie will need to be an only dog, but do not worry this is how she prefers to live. All attention will be hers. She is housebroken and will have no problem adjusting to a new home. If love is what you want, Smushie is what you need.

OPERATION SMUSHIE IS UNDERWAY!
Smushie came to ARF over five years ago, and sadly, she remains one of our longest residents at the Adoption Center. As a friend of ARF, you have probably met or heard of Smushie. With more than 2,000 days at the shelter, she continues to be overlooked making ARF more determined than ever to find her a home in 2020! We have made this our mission for these final weeks of 2020, calling it Operation Smushie, and we need your help! 

Whether it is her size, or her breed, or the fact that she needs to be the only pet in the home, Smushie continues to be passed over by potential adopters. We will not stop until Smushie has a home. 

Please help us spread the word about this beautiful girl, and together we can give her the life she has been patiently waiting for!

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Buster and I am a 5-year-old Labrador Retriever mix with a heart as golden as my shiny coat. I am desperately searching for my next best friend and hope it's YOU. I was adopted as a young pup and really looked forward to meeting new people, going places, and interacting with other dogs. Unfortunately, my people just didn't give me the time and patience I needed to explore the world. Rather, they threw me quickly into unfamiliar situations that made me anxious and nervous. When I indicated that I was scared, they gave up on me and isolated me from the experiences I desperately needed. So here I am, 4 years old, and learning manners and socialization skills like those little puppies do. The good news is, I'm nailing it and am an excellent student! I am very quick to pick up on basic obedience and have already mastered several tricks. While I love to meet new people, I need a slow introduction to ensure I find them to be trustworthy and kind. Positive experiences and controlled repetition are boosting my confidence tremendously. I will thrive in a predictable, structured environment with adopters who understand my need for a little extra time. 

I am desperate to please my favorite humans and have really improved my leash skills. I really enjoy my walks now that I am engaged with the person at the other end of the leash. I am very treat motivated and also enjoy words of affirmation. Seriously, "Good Boy!" is like music to my ears! All I ask is that you take the time to show me what you expect and then hold me to those expectations. I crave structure and leadership and respond very well to both. I would love for my new person to engage in training with me to continue what Ive been learning and the rescue said theyll introduce whoever adopts me to the trainer who has worked with me. Please take a chance on me, I promise you a lifetime of loyalty and friendship. 

*Homeownership required!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration

animal.description:
Hi, Im Brownie! Everyone that meets me keeps using this word sweetI think thats a good thing, right? All I know is that I love being around all those 2-legged creatures with the leashes and the food. They are so snuggly! And delicious, tooI really like giving them kisses.

 

I dont mind being in a crate. Its even kind of my happy place. The ones with the leashes and the food tell me that Im bombproof. I dont know what that means, but I do know that I can handle anything that might stress a lot of other dogs out. Pretty sure thats because I spent a lot of time on the tough streets of Houston growing up. Those 2-leggeds werent always so nice to me down there, but that doesnt even matter anymore because I love EVERYONE I meet.

 

The folks with the leashes say that I could use a little more practice at the other end of the leash. They tell me Im getting better at it all the time, and we just keep walking and walking and walking. I hope someday I can go walking with YOU too! Oh, and get thiswe tried walking on this thing called a treadmill recently. Its where you just walk in the same place without going anywhere. At first I thought it was a little silly, but I started to get the hang of it before too long and want to try it some more. Do you have one of those things in your home, because I would love some more practice?

 

Here are some of my favorite things: belly rubs, naps, and laps! Wait, there is also this stuff called snow that is waaaaay fun to roll around in. We sure didnt have that where I came from! I love it so much here, and those 2-leggeds say that my tail NEVER stops wagging. Im just a happy girlwhat can I say? 

*Homeownership required!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

animal.description:
Carolina Boxer Rescue is a volunteer run, 501(c)3 non-profit organization. Our mission: To balance the health, safety, and welfare needs of Boxers in the Carolinas (and parts of Virginia and Georgia) by providing a loving and safe environment for stray, abused, impounded and owner surrendered dogs by placing them in foster homes and ultimately - forever homes.

________________________________________________________________________________________

Dog's Name: Cotton

Dog's Approximate Age: 10 years

Gender: Female

Dog's Size: Medium (50lbs to 70lbs. as adult and healthy weight)

Dog's Weight: 70 pounds

Good with small dogs?: No

Good with big dogs?: No

Good with cats?: Yes

Good with kids?: Don't know yet

Any medical issues?: Cotton was recently diagnosed with mammary tumors, which is common in dogs that are not spayed.

Crate trained?: Yes

House trained?: Yes

Heartworms?: Yes

10/22/20: Hi there, it's Cotton! Just want to share a quick update on how things are going here in Wilmington.

I've started my slow kill heartworm treatment, and I've added a third member to my pack- she's a raccoon but I love her like a pup! Taking naps with my pack is one of my favorite things to do.

Over the past few weeks, it felt right to let my FM get to know me better- I've shown her a few tricks that I know including sit, lay down, and shake.

I've still never had an accident in the house or caused any damage. When it's time to go out, I let my FM know, and if I feel like delicately chewing on something, it's always on a member of my pack.

Even though I'm in the double-digits, I'm strong for my age. I really enjoy walks in our neighborhood, so I'm going to practice walking with a harness over the next few weeks. Keep your paws crossed for me!

TTYL!

8/31/20: Cotton arrived at her foster home gently carrying her stuffed animal baby by the scruff of its neck. Although she seemed timid, it didn't take her long to warm up to her new foster mom. A husky and newly added rottweiler make up her pack of stuffed animal babies, and her favorite thing to do is cuddle next to her human and her babies. Cotton is gentle with all things, and throughout all her travels, she has not injured her stuffed animals and treats them like her pups.

Likely kept outside on a leash in her former life, she prefers brief trips outside these days and she politely lets you know when it's time for quick trip. She is house trained as we have not had a single accident since we've had her. She is also crate trained, and she will sleep through the night in her crate with no issues. She is Heart worm Positive and is being treated.

Although this senior lady is quiet and gentle with everything around her, she seems leery of other dogs, and would be okay if it were just her and her forever human.

_________

8/14/20: Welcome Cottonella to CBR. More to come as she gets settled into her foster home.

_____________________________________________________________________________

Come visit carolinaboxerrescue.org to learn more about me and see more pictures. Learn about our adoption process too!

_____________________________________________________________________________

Bond is about 2 yrs old and was found as a stray in the rescue center parking lot.  He wandered up and we worked for a couple of days for him to come inside and join the dog party.  Being a bit of a mystery, we decided Bond, James Bond was a fitting name for him.

He likes other dogs, but is a little hesitant with new people at the moment and does need someone with a little patience with him. He's curious and you can tell he wants to love you- he just hasn’t been treated well by people in the past.  He needs a foster to help him transition to the next phase of his new awesome life. He deserves  to couch to nap on too.

Thanks for considering a Cane Rosso Rescue dog! 
We place dogs mostly in Texas but have adopted out a few out-of-state as well.
 
If you are interested in one of our dogs, please first complete our adoption application.
You can find it at https://www.canerossorescue.org/adoption-application . His adoption fee is $300 plus tax. Our dogs are spayed or neutered, microchipped, vaccinated and heartworm tested and treated (if tested positive) before going to a new home. or email us at rescue@canerosso.com.

animal.description:
This sweet boy was surrendered to us when his owner passed away. The owner’s son who is homeless and knew he couldn’t give him the quality of life he so deserves, cared enough about him to make sure he got into our rescue where he would be cared for and assisted in finding his new forever home. 

As far as personalities go, this boy is a gem. He gets along well with people, dogs and doesn’t even have a problem if there’s a proven dog-friendly cat around. He loves his belly rubs and attention but is also independent and doesn’t mind being on his own for periods of time. He is a good passenger in the car and has a favourite green toy he takes outside every time he goes out. 

At 8 years old Pinceau has some aches, pains and medical conditions that often accompany a senior dog. He does have arthritis in his hips so he’s not a runner or a hiker. He really likes his walks but is not high energy. He has been receiving some injections and oral medications that have been making him feel better. He will need to continue with the prescribed course so he can enjoy his life as pain free as possible. He has also been experiencing some urinary dribbles and we are in the midst of starting him on a medication to see if that will improve. For now he is sporting some doggy diapers and looking oh so adorable! 

Pinceau is also on a special gastro diet as he experienced some tummy upset from some of the non-prescription foods. 

To make sure he is kept as healthy as possible he will need annual bloodwork, annual urine testing, monthly injections for his hips and a few oral medications. The monthly costs for all of the above, including his prescription food is approximately $275.00. 

Senior dogs make wonderful companions and are forever grateful. If you have a calm environment, no stairs (or very few stairs), don’t mind administering some medication and getting some love and wet kisses in return, this boy may be for you!

animal.description:
Stevie (Nicks)  is from our musical legends litter. 10 puppies named after famous musicians. They had a very rough beginning, but have flourished in foster care the past few months learning how to dog. They were born in January 2020. 

Stevie has perfect manners with other dogs and would really thrive in a home with another confident dog to play with.. Stevie can be shy/fearful around new people and men.  She enjoys going for walks, playing fetch and loves learning new things. She will do anything for a tennis ball! She is extremely smart and would benefit from taking our professional dog training classes with her adopter so you guys can learn all the things together. Learn more about our classes at unchainedmelodies.org

Stevie has a moderate to high activity level and would make a great adventure buddy. 

Fun Facts:

Age (best guess) - 1 year
Breed (best guess) - Cattle Dog Mix
Current Weight - 45
Dog Friendly - Yes
Cat Friendly - No
Kid Friendly - No
Potty Trained - Yes
Crate Trained - Yes
Leash Trained - Yes

All of our adult dogs are current on vaccinations, de-wormed, heart worm tested, spayed/neutered, on monthly preventatives & micro chipped prior to adoption. 

*Adoption Fee is $200.00, No out of State Adoptions ,Virtual Home Visits 
 Required  

*We do not require fenced yards for all dogs, fenced yards are required based on a dogs needs. *No invisible fences.

Thank you for adopting!

animal.description:
Hoping to find a trainer willing to save Millie. Millie is a loving terrorist? If this makes sense to you then she's the one that needs you. Millie will chase everything. She's very high energy and needs an experienced adopter to help work with her. When inside and in the house on the couch she's the most loving dog ever. We can not recommend children or other dogs due to her not being able to control her energy. She was raised with other dogs and cats and most of the time she's fine with them but one dog she got into with and she wouldn't stop when told and had to hold her back for some time before she would settle down. Can you help her?
https://www.causendogrescue.org/adoption-application.html

If you rent or own a home, we prefer you to have a fenced in yard.
Apartment living is also ok but prefer a fenced in area if open to the road.
All adults in the home will need to know they are getting a dog and will need to sign the adoption agreement.
We will not adopt to college students with multiple roommates.
Military will need to provide a backup plan.
We require all pets in the home to be spay and neutered. Because to many dogs are being killed, due to there not being enough homes per dog in need. Only the lucky ones end up here.

animal.description:
Meet Indigo! 

Mr. Indi was an owner surrender & came to Take Paws only a week(ish) ago! 
He is about 4 yrs old. UTD on shots, HW negative & neutered. 

He may seem all large and in charge, but, this dude will win you over with his nugget size & potato-like body. 

Like any potato, he takes his time warming up to new people, but once he does, he is hooked and awaits your snuggles and attention. His affection cannot be bought with treats ( although I'm sure it wouldn't hurt) but he'd rather know that he is safe, loved and can hang out with you while you work or play. 

He is great with other dogs, lived with cats, and ok with kids. He is not a jumpy fella. If you're looking to add an additional member to your family, Indigo is waiting! 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our dogs are healthy, spayed/neutered, vaccinated and on heartworm preventative. They live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. Many have basic obedience skills and all have been temperament tested. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, please visit our website to complete an application: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt
(please note: app cannot be done on a mobile device)

For additional information see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Meet Bickman!! He is a 5 year-old neutered 81lb standard Australian Shepherd??. Bickman is up-to-date on vaccines and preventative?s. Looking for his new forever family he’s a happy boy and constantly a wiggle butt?! 

Bickmans ideal home? Is an active family with older children and a large fenced yard as he loves to run and also needs to exercise to help get him back down to his ideal weight?. He also would need to be the only dog in the household as two years ago he was attacked by another dog and has become fearful aggressive towards other dogs.  He has been with a trainer last year to work through these issues and he can now walk by other dogs and ignore them and even greet them properly through fences and gates. He also went through training to become a diabetic alert dog for his previous owner who unfortunately has been permanently hospitalized from her terrible disease?. 

His perfect family will get to do a lesson with his trainer. Bickman also ignores the cat Brody at his vets office but it’s unsure how he would do living with one so best a home without any. Bickman loves his people and really all people.

Bickman will absolutely not be able to live In An apartment he needs exercise and lots of play and adventures!! He is being fostered in Auburn GA

If you think Bickman is the right fit for your family, please fill out our application:

https://www.australianshepherdsfurever.org/adoption-application

All adoption fees are used for future rescue efforts.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Tommy, and I'm a new addition to Pawmetto Lifeline. My adoption fee of $200 includes my neuter surgery, deworming, microchip, and up-to-date vaccinations. 

I am a recent tripod due to an accident before my time at PLL and I am working on my social skills. I'll be a good boy but I need a bit to warm up to my new family! Because of how shy I am, I'd prefer to be in a home without any small children. 

I am currently in a foster home, which means I am not on site at Pawmetto Lifeline and am staying with someone volunteering their time and their home. If you'd like to meet, please mention it in your application so we can set up an appointment for me to be brought to the facility.

My adoption is considered "Best Match". This means that I am looking for a specific type of home or certain qualities in my new family. I am not first come-first serve for any approved applicant. Pawmetto Lifeline's adoption advocates and my case managers would love to review your application to see if we are a good fit. I appreciate your patience as the Adoption team discusses your application with my case managers!

I've even started on my monthly flea and heartworm preventatives - what more could you ask for? If you'd like to meet me, please fill out an online application and an advocate will be with you shortly.

animal.description: Babs is a sweet tempered perfect size dog who loves to have her tummy rubbed. She is very easy going almost all of the time, but will go after wildlife that is invading her (your) yard. She mostly loves hanging out with you on comfy cushions. She has a sensitive nose which seems to be her main way of seeing the world. On walks she will sniff anything interesting which is everything. She has a hypothyroid condition which is controlled with a twice daily pill which I usually give her in a small amount of peanut butter before her regular meal. Because of her condition, she is a little overweight right now. She will eat almost anything in your yard so I keep a close eye on her when she is out. She likes to bark at the dog next door and the feeling is mutual, but she will stop when told to. She is playful and likes chasing balls and playing tug of war. She is a great companion!She is great with humans - sweet, gentle, obedient, easily trusting. She only barks when someone approaches the door (and has even stopped doing that when it's someone she knows). We are working on sit, down and stay commands with some success! She is very food motivated.She loves belly rubs and even sits in my lap about once a day though she enjoys her space as well and doesn't need constant attention. Her ideal home and human:-No other dogs. No matter the size or how frequently she is introduced to the same one, she will consistently be quiet as they approach her and then snap at/snarl when they get too close. She is also highly distracted by dogs and the smell of dogs at the park so she braces and refuses to walk there.-She loves a daily small amount of playing fetch or tug-of-war with her human. This is her primary exercise as she hasn't been a fan of being outside or walking for very long.-She is completely house trained. Even when she was having diarrhea every day for weeks - she would hold it til she was outside. -I tried crating her, but she panted the whole time so I didn't try it for very long. During my 5-7 hour work shift she had free reign of my small home with no issues for the past two months. I didn't invite her to sleep in my bed, but she usually chooses to be in the same room as me when I am home.-She is 8-10 years old and rests a lot. Occasionally has bouts of energy where she is running and jumping and still has an intense hunting instinct when she smells rabbits in the yard.-She was a stray and tends to try to eat whatever she can find outside and has a sensitive stomach so she should be supervised outside.-Now that we've identified some of her health solutions, she is a pretty easy dog!Meds:-She has hypothyroidism, which should account for some of the exercise intolerance, extra weight and the fur loss that she has been experiencing. She takes one medication (Soloxine) twice a day for this and will need to take it daily Perhaps Babs doesnt look any thinner but she perks up when we are headed outside. Absolutely LOVES walks. Her downward dog was horrid on May 6, but before May 31st her butt couldnt get any higher and boy can she stretch! This is a very happy dog with lots of playfullness in her.

animal.description: Lady is a loving senior girl with a heartbreaking story. She was left in an apartment to fend for herself for over a month after her owner was taken to the hospital - her owner thought her adult child was taking care of her but he wasn't! When the neighbors finally realized no one was entering the apartment they had the door unlocked only to find Lady wilting away...all the water from the toilet bowl was gone ( she had drank it) and a bag of dog food was empty ( her only food source)...and to make matters more distressing, poor Lady, who is vision impaired and 13 years young, was covered in urine and feces and matted beyond recognition. We will not post pictures of when she was found. THAT IS THE PAST! We will post pictures of our beautiful Lady as she is NOW our promise to her is a loving and caring forever home. Her owner never lived to know the hardship her poor baby suffered but we are sure she is looking down from heaven and seeing the care she is receiving now. Lady is a sweet and delightful well behaved girl...she gets along well with other dogs but NO KIDS. If interested i giving this special girl the loving home she rightfully deserves please fill out an application at www.floridacockerrescue.org ADOPTION FEE: $175.00

animal.description: Tyson is a gorgeous, brindle guy. He likes to play with toys, has some doggie friends, and tries to keep his kennel clean. He's such a smart boy. He knows some basic commands, like sit and stay. He took a day trip to a volunteer's house and did great! He was unsure when he first went into the house (we don't think he has lived in one), but then he opened up and thoroughly enjoyed himself. He found the toy box. That was like Christmas to Tyson! What a blast! Tyson is also part of our Pets in Progress Program where special needs pets get extra assistance from staff and volunteers. If you are interested in more info about Tyson, contact our Behavior Team. Dog selective. No cats. No children.

Special Adoption Opportunity! ---

Kylie is a playful, sweet lady who loves to lay by her human's side, play in the yard, and be with her foster siblings. Kylie has been up north since January, and she is a totally different dog these days. She is timid and anxious around new people and in new situations, but give her time and share some cheese and she'll warm up to you- and others- in no time. She is very gentle, house trained, listens great and does well with routine! She gets along great with other dogs- they play, share toys, and Kylie follows them around a lot. Kylie loves being around her house mates so much, so she is still working a bit on her separation anxiety in the crate. She can be left for several hours at a time but may bark. She will need continued training to settle in the crate, even when her humans are around, and will likely be a better fit for a home where she wont bother neighbors. She likes walks but is still getting used to being on a leash in noisy areas. Having a yard would be pretty ideal! Kylie has so much love to give, and with just a little patience she will be sure to shower you with it. She cant wait to meet her FURever family.

---Kylie is currently undergoing Heartworm treatment and while she has finished the bulk of it, she does have some minor medical care to complete. She is available for a medical foster who will eventually adopt her once she is medically cleared. All medical costs during this treatment are covered by LHK9. Any potential adopter would need to be available to take her to Heal Veterinary Clinic in Watertown for monthly blood tests until she is all clear. Please email Adoptions@lasthopek9.org if you are interested!
